A 17-year-old boy was hanged in public in the holy  city of Masshad after being found guilty of raping an 11-year-old schoolgirl,  newspapers said Tuesday.
The boy "confessed" in court to having raped the girl in an empty lot as  she went to school in Mashhad, site of a holy Shiite Moslem shrine, the papers  said.
A crowd watched as he was hanged in a public square on Monday.
